        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:21PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms over Woodrow, or 23 miles southeast of Fort Morgan,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Akron, Woodrow and Shamrock.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
